{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f5012de9-b7b9-4210-93b4-b2a8f386de29","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Dockerfile additions:**\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:8.0-alpine\n\n# Create a writable dumps directory\nRUN mkdir -p /tmp/dumps && chmod 777 /tmp/dumps\n\n# Enable automatic crash dump collection\nENV DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nENV DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4\nENV DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\n\n# Switch to non-root user\nUSER app\n```\n\n| Variable | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `DbgEnableMiniDump=1` | Enable crash dumps |\n| `DbgMiniDumpType=4` | Full dump (1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full) |\n| `DbgMiniDumpName` | Dump path (`%p`=PID, `%t`=timestamp) |\n\n**docker run command:**\n\n```bash\ndocker run --cap-add=SYS_PTRACE \\\n  -v /host/path/to/dumps:/tmp/dumps \\\n  your-image\n```\n\n`--cap-add=SYS_PTRACE` is **required** — CoreCLR's `createdump` tool uses `ptrace` to capture the dump, and Docker drops this capability by default.\n\nThe bind mount lets you retrieve dumps from the host after a crash.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fd436d01-fa3a-405f-bd5a-a735e29a573c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up crash dump collection for a CoreCLR/.NET app running in an Alpine-based Docker container with a non-root user. I'll provide the Dockerfile changes and `docker run` command needed.\n\nKey considerations for Alpine + CoreCLR crash dumps:\n- Alpine uses musl libc, not glibc — createdump is the .NET-provided tool\n- Need `ptrace` capability for createdump to work\n- Need a writable directory for dumps\n- Environment variables to configure dump collection\n- SYS_PTRACE capability needed at `docker run`\n- /tmp/dumps or similar directory with correct permissions","outputTokens":518,"requestId":"6013:15FDF:DEEDD7:1027DF4:69EACB39"},"id":"6fc5a150-ffd7-456d-a764-c95bcad9f4d1","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:45:40.992Z","parentId":"43349b19-4312-414f-b538-28e9402f090e"}
